{
  "number": 6569,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/6569",
  "title": "feat: make events default implementation compatible with composition API",
  "body": "**Summary**\r\n\r\n[EMERCH-1902](https://algolia.atlassian.net/browse/EMERCH-1902)\r\n\r\nUpdate events default implementation to make it compatible with Composition API, _i.e._\r\n\r\nBefore:\r\n- events are sending an `index` property\r\n- it currently often relies on `getIndex()` which returns the `compositionID` when using the Composition implementation of InstantSearch\r\n- this results in events being \"lost\" as the insights API is not aware of Compositions\r\n\r\nAfter:\r\n- when sending events, for the `index` property,\r\n- first rely on the `index` property in the results (id present)\r\n- only rely on `getIndex()` as a fallback\r\n\r\n**Result**\r\n- when using the index implementation, nothing should change\r\n- when using the composition implementation, the main index (send under `results.index` in the API response) is used when sending events (previsously composition ID)\n\n[EMERCH-1902]: https://algolia.atlassian.net/browse/EMERCH-1902?atlOrigin=eyJpIjoiNWRkNTljNzYxNjVmNDY3MDlhMDU5Y2ZhYzA5YTRkZjUiLCJwIjoiZ2l0aHViLWNvbS1KU1cifQ",
